Commercial crops include citrus fruits, sugar cane, sweet potatoes, peaches and grapes. Sichuan also had the largest output of <a2_0><b11_0>pork<b11_0/><a2_0/> among all the provinces and the second largest output of silkworm cocoons in 1999. Sichuan is rich in mineral resources. It has more than 132 kinds of proven underground mineral resources including vanadium, titanium, and lithium being the largest in China. The <b8_0>Panxi<b8_0/> region alone possesses 13.3% of the reserves of iron, <a3_0><b12_0>93%<b12_0/><a3_0/> of titanium, 69% of vanadium, and 83% of the cobalt of the whole country.
